.SH NAME
.PP
envctl-env-delete - Delete an environment from the project


.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBenvctl env delete  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Delete an environment and all its variables.

.PP
This removes the environment definition from the project. Any secrets
stored in this environment will no longer be accessible.

.PP
Use --force to also revoke access from members who have access to this environment.

.PP
Examples:
  envctl env delete staging
  envctl env delete old-env --force


.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	force remove and revoke access from members

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for delete


